Principal component analysis

stat_pca.Rd

Performs a principal components analysis (delegated to stats::prcomp).

stat_pca(x, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE)

Arguments

x

coe_tbl
center

logical whether the variables should be shifted to be zero centered (center in stats::prcomp)
scale

logical whether the variables should be scaled to have unit variance before the analysis takes place (scale. in stats::prcomp)

Value

object of class pca, a tibble::tibble with attributes

References

stats::prcomp

Examples

(x <-  bot2 %>% efourier(4) %>% stat_pca())
